00:00:40.736 --> 00:00:50.144
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:50.112 --> 00:01:00.160
You know, the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:59.680 --> 00:01:08.416
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:01:09.632 --> 00:01:12.032
The dream of Pilate's wife.

00:01:12.736 --> 00:01:14.880
A sermon by Charles Spurgeon.

00:01:15.136 --> 00:01:16.256
Part one.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:20.416
When he was sat down on the judgment seat,

00:01:20.448 --> 00:01:23.232
His wife sent unto him, saying,

00:01:23.008 --> 00:01:25.984
Have nothing to do with that just man.

00:01:26.368 --> 00:01:29.792
For I have suffered many things this day in a dream.

00:01:29.728 --> 00:01:31.072
Because of him.

00:01:32.064 --> 00:01:34.752
Matthew's Gospel, chapter 27.

00:01:34.816 --> 00:01:36.608
Verse nineteen.

00:01:37.824 --> 00:01:44.192
I earnestly wished to pursue the story of our saviour's trials previous to his crucifixion.

00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:47.488
But when I sat down to study the subject,

00:01:47.808 --> 00:01:51.712
I found myself altogether incapable of the exercise.

00:01:52.704 --> 00:01:56.768
When I thought to know this, it was too painful for me.

00:01:56.928 --> 00:01:59.456
My emotions grew so strong

00:01:59.264 --> 00:02:03.456
And my sense of our Lord's grief became so extremely vivid.

00:02:03.648 --> 00:02:06.976
That I felt I must waive the subject for a time.

00:02:07.552 --> 00:02:10.464
I could not watch with him another hour.

00:02:10.656 --> 00:02:15.648
And yet I could not leave the hallowed scene. It was therefore a relief.

00:02:15.584 --> 00:02:19.360
to meet with the episode of Pilot's wife and her dream.

00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:23.328
It enables me to continue the thread of my narrative.

00:02:23.424 --> 00:02:24.544
And yet,

00:02:24.384 --> 00:02:30.976
To relax the extreme tension of the feelings caused by a near view of the master's grief and shame.

00:02:31.680 --> 00:02:34.912
My spirit failed before the terrible sight.

00:02:35.488 --> 00:02:41.152
I thought I saw him brought back from Herod, where the men of war had set him at naught.

00:02:41.376 --> 00:02:45.408
I followed him through the streets again as the cruel priests,

00:02:45.152 --> 00:02:49.216
Pushed through the crowd and hastened him back to Pilate's hall.

00:02:49.792 --> 00:02:52.224
I thought I heard them in the streets.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:55.296
electing Barabbas the robber to be set free.

00:02:55.232 --> 00:02:57.600
Instead of Jesus, the Savior.

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:01.952
And I detected the first rising of that awful cry.

00:03:01.920 --> 00:03:03.072
Crucify.

00:03:03.296 --> 00:03:04.512
Crucify

00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:08.384
Which they shrieked out from their bloodthirsty throats.

00:03:09.088 --> 00:03:10.816
And there he stood,

00:03:10.944 --> 00:03:12.224
Who loved me?

00:03:12.288 --> 00:03:14.336
And gave himself for me.

00:03:14.336 --> 00:03:16.960
Like a lamb in the midst of wolves,

00:03:16.832 --> 00:03:18.656
With none to pity.

00:03:18.528 --> 00:03:20.192
And none to help him.

00:03:21.312 --> 00:03:23.392
The vision overwhelmed me.

00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.368
especially when I knew that the next stage

00:03:26.016 --> 00:03:30.240
"'Would be the pilot who had exculpated him by declaring, "'I'm

00:03:29.984 --> 00:03:32.512
I find no fault in him.

00:03:32.992 --> 00:03:35.616
Would give him over to the tormentors.

00:03:35.392 --> 00:03:37.408
That he might be scourged.

00:03:37.664 --> 00:03:39.808
That the mercenary soldiery,

00:03:39.776 --> 00:03:43.744
Would crown him with thorns, and mercilessly insult him.

00:03:44.192 --> 00:03:47.424
And that he would be brought forth to the people.

00:03:47.552 --> 00:03:49.632
And announced to them.

00:03:49.568 --> 00:03:53.248
With that heartrending word, behold the man!

00:03:53.728 --> 00:03:57.184
Was there ever sorrow like unto his sorrow?

00:03:57.856 --> 00:04:00.448
We leave the master awhile to look,

00:04:00.288 --> 00:04:02.848
At this dream of Pilate's wife.

00:04:02.912 --> 00:04:05.920
Which is only spoken of once in the scriptures.

00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:07.744
And then by Matthew.

00:04:08.288 --> 00:04:11.648
I know not why that evangelist only.

00:04:11.488 --> 00:04:14.368
Should have been commissioned to record it.

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:17.376
Perhaps he alone heard of it.

00:04:17.344 --> 00:04:20.544
But the one record is sufficient for our faith.

00:04:20.416 --> 00:04:21.664
And long enough.

00:04:21.632 --> 00:04:24.320
To furnish food for meditation.

00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:28.896
We receive the story as certified by the Holy Spirit.

00:04:30.016 --> 00:04:31.008
Pilot,

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:34.912
Throughout his term of office had grossly misbehaved himself.

00:04:35.456 --> 00:04:40.128
He had been an unjust and unscrupulous ruler of the Jews,

00:04:40.192 --> 00:04:45.216
The Galileans and the Samaritans both felt the terror of his arms.

00:04:45.568 --> 00:04:47.552
For he did not hesitate.

00:04:47.456 --> 00:04:51.104
To massacre them at the slightest sign of revolt.

00:04:51.424 --> 00:04:58.464
And among the Jews themselves, he had sent men with daggers into the midst of the crowds at the great gatherings.

00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:00.480
And so had cut off.

00:05:00.256 --> 00:05:02.752
Those who were obnoxious to him.

00:05:03.776 --> 00:05:04.800
gain

00:05:04.704 --> 00:05:06.112
Was his object?

00:05:05.984 --> 00:05:08.480
And pride ruled his spirit.

00:05:09.248 --> 00:05:11.936
At the time when Jesus of Nazareth

00:05:11.808 --> 00:05:13.664
Was brought before him.

00:05:13.536 --> 00:05:17.792
A complaint against him was on the way to Tiberius the Emperor.

00:05:17.696 --> 00:05:19.104
And he feared.

00:05:19.072 --> 00:05:21.536
Lest he should be called to account,

00:05:21.344 --> 00:05:24.800
For his oppressions, extortions and murders.

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:29.472
His sins at this moment were beginning to punish him.

00:05:29.504 --> 00:05:31.584
As Job would word it,

00:05:31.456 --> 00:05:34.976
The iniquities of his heels compassed him about.

00:05:35.616 --> 00:05:38.848
One terrible portion of the penalty of sin,

00:05:38.912 --> 00:05:43.808
Is its power to force a man to commit yet further iniquity.

00:05:44.352 --> 00:05:49.696
Pilate's transgressions were now howling around him like a pack of wolves.

00:05:49.824 --> 00:05:51.712
He could not face them.

00:05:51.744 --> 00:05:56.480
And he had not grace to flee to the one great refuge.

00:05:56.960 --> 00:06:00.160
But his fears drove him to flee before them.

00:06:00.224 --> 00:06:07.744
And there was no way apparently open for him but that which led him into yet deeper abominations.

00:06:07.936 --> 00:06:11.808
He knew that Jesus was without a single fault.

00:06:12.288 --> 00:06:13.376
And yet,

00:06:13.184 --> 00:06:15.904
Since the Jews clamoured for his death,

00:06:16.128 --> 00:06:19.552
He felt that he must yield to their demands.

00:06:19.744 --> 00:06:20.864
Or else,

00:06:20.608 --> 00:06:26.048
They would raise another accusation against himself, namely that he was not loyal.

00:06:26.048 --> 00:06:28.352
To the sovereignty of Caesar.

00:06:28.640 --> 00:06:31.136
For he had allowed one to escape,

00:06:31.136 --> 00:06:33.376
Who had called himself a king?

00:06:33.888 --> 00:06:36.192
If he had behaved justly,

00:06:36.192 --> 00:06:40.544
He would not have been afraid of the chief priests and scribes.

00:06:41.216 --> 00:06:43.264
Innocence is brave.

00:06:43.552 --> 00:06:44.704
But guilt,

00:06:44.544 --> 00:06:45.952
Is cowardly.

00:06:46.688 --> 00:06:49.664
The pilot's old sins found him out.

00:06:49.440 --> 00:06:53.248
And made him weak in the presence of the ignoble crew.

00:06:53.152 --> 00:06:56.832
Whom otherwise he would have driven from the judgment seat.

00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:59.648
He had power enough.

00:06:59.648 --> 00:07:01.472
To have silenced them.

00:07:01.984 --> 00:07:05.056
But he had not sufficient decision of character.

00:07:05.056 --> 00:07:07.136
To end the contention.

00:07:07.520 --> 00:07:10.080
The power was gone from his mind.

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.416
Because he knew that his conduct

00:07:12.224 --> 00:07:14.720
Would not bear investigation.

00:07:14.880 --> 00:07:17.600
And he dreaded the loss of his office.

00:07:17.568 --> 00:07:20.960
Which he held only for his own ends.

00:07:21.792 --> 00:07:23.776
See there with pity,

00:07:23.648 --> 00:07:28.992
That scornful but vacillating creature wavering in the presence of men.

00:07:28.704 --> 00:07:31.168
Who were more wicked than himself,

00:07:31.072 --> 00:07:33.792
And more determined in their purpose.

00:07:34.976 --> 00:07:38.240
The feral determination of the wicked priests

00:07:38.272 --> 00:07:40.864
Caused hesitating policy,

00:07:40.672 --> 00:07:42.976
To quail in their presence.

00:07:43.072 --> 00:07:44.288
And pilot

00:07:44.320 --> 00:07:46.176
Was driven to do.

00:07:45.952 --> 00:07:48.224
What he would gladly have avoided.

00:07:50.176 --> 00:07:54.016
The manner and the words of Jesus had impressed Pilate.

00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:56.416
I say the manner of Jesus

00:07:56.224 --> 00:08:03.168
For his matchless meekness must have struck the governor as being a very unusual thing in a prisoner.

00:08:03.904 --> 00:08:07.104
He had seen in captured Jews.

00:08:07.136 --> 00:08:09.696
The fierce courage of fanaticism

00:08:10.272 --> 00:08:13.216
But there was no fanaticism in Christ.

00:08:13.824 --> 00:08:16.480
He had also seen in many prisoners

00:08:16.608 --> 00:08:21.728
The meanness which will do or say anything to escape from death.

00:08:22.304 --> 00:08:25.216
But he saw nothing of that about our Lord.

00:08:25.920 --> 00:08:29.632
He saw in him unusual gentleness,

00:08:29.376 --> 00:08:30.784
And humility.

00:08:31.008 --> 00:08:33.824
Combined with majestic dignity.

00:08:34.816 --> 00:08:38.656
He beheld submission blended with innocence.

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:42.112
This made pilot feel how awful.

00:08:41.920 --> 00:08:43.488
Goodness is.

00:08:43.872 --> 00:08:45.440
He was impressed.

00:08:45.472 --> 00:08:47.872
He could not help being impressed.

00:08:47.744 --> 00:08:50.208
With this unique sufferer.

00:08:51.360 --> 00:08:52.608
Besides,

00:08:52.512 --> 00:08:56.320
Our Lord had before him witnessed a good confession,

00:08:56.896 --> 00:08:59.776
You remember how we considered it the other day.

00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:03.776
and though pilot had huffed it off with the pert question

00:09:03.552 --> 00:09:05.408
What is truth?

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:08.480
And had gone back into the Judgment hall.

00:09:08.672 --> 00:09:10.336
Yet there was an arrow,

00:09:10.272 --> 00:09:13.568
Fixed within him which he could not shake off.

00:09:14.528 --> 00:09:17.568
It may have been mainly superstition.

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:19.680
But he felt an awe.

00:09:19.584 --> 00:09:22.400
Of one whom he half expected.

00:09:22.272 --> 00:09:24.864
To be an extraordinary personage.

00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:30.752
He felt that he himself was placed in a very extraordinary position.

00:09:30.592 --> 00:09:33.376
Being asked to condemn one

00:09:33.184 --> 00:09:36.032
Whom he knew to be perfectly innocent.

00:09:36.864 --> 00:09:38.976
His duty was clear enough.

00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:42.112
He could never have had a question about that.

00:09:42.496 --> 00:09:45.088
But duty was nothing to Pilate.

00:09:45.472 --> 00:09:48.256
In comparison with his own interests.

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:51.488
He would spare the just one.

00:09:51.392 --> 00:09:54.656
If he could do so without endangering himself.

00:09:54.656 --> 00:09:58.048
But his cowardly fears lashed him on.

00:09:57.920 --> 00:10:00.576
To the shedding of innocent blood.

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:03.488
At the very moment

00:10:03.392 --> 00:10:05.216
When he was vacillating

00:10:05.536 --> 00:10:08.224
When he had offered to the Jews,

00:10:08.032 --> 00:10:11.520
The choice of Barabbas or Jesus of Nazareth,

00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.888
At that very moment, I say,

00:10:14.432 --> 00:10:17.376
When he had taken his seat upon the bench,

00:10:17.344 --> 00:10:19.680
And was waiting for their choice.

00:10:19.872 --> 00:10:22.304
There came from the hand of God

00:10:22.272 --> 00:10:24.096
A warning to him.

00:10:24.384 --> 00:10:25.696
A warning.

00:10:25.440 --> 00:10:28.256
Which would for ever make it clear.

00:10:28.352 --> 00:10:30.816
That if he condemned Jesus,

00:10:30.624 --> 00:10:32.832
It would be done voluntarily.

00:10:32.672 --> 00:10:35.136
By his own guilty hands.

00:10:36.320 --> 00:10:38.464
Jesus must die.

00:10:38.304 --> 00:10:42.112
by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God.

00:10:41.952 --> 00:10:46.496
And yet it must be by wicked hands that he is crucified.

00:10:46.272 --> 00:10:47.552
And slain.

00:10:48.096 --> 00:10:49.344
And hence,

00:10:49.216 --> 00:10:52.320
Pilate must not sin in ignorance.

00:10:52.704 --> 00:10:54.592
A warning to pilot

00:10:54.656 --> 00:10:58.656
Came from his own wife concerning her morning's dream.

00:10:58.592 --> 00:11:00.992
A vision of mystery and terror.

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:04.704
Warning him not to touch that just person.

00:11:05.088 --> 00:11:06.624
For sechi,

00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:10.496
"I have suffered many things this day in a dream."

00:11:10.464 --> 00:11:11.840
Because of him.

00:11:12.704 --> 00:11:17.280
There are times in most men's lives when though they have been wrong,

00:11:17.312 --> 00:11:20.832
Yet they have not quite been set on mischief.

00:11:21.152 --> 00:11:23.264
But have come to a pause.

00:11:23.616 --> 00:11:26.432
And have deliberated as to their way.

00:11:27.648 --> 00:11:31.520
And then God in great mercy has sent them a caution.

00:11:31.456 --> 00:11:33.984
And has set up a danger signal.

00:11:33.888 --> 00:11:36.800
Bidding them stop in their mad career.

00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:41.280
Ere they plunged themselves finally into irretrievable ruin.

00:11:41.696 --> 00:11:42.752
Somewhere,

00:11:42.784 --> 00:11:46.944
In that direction lies the subject of our present discourse.

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:49.248
Oh that the spirit of god

00:11:49.184 --> 00:11:51.680
May make it useful to many.

00:11:52.384 --> 00:11:53.696
And first

00:11:53.696 --> 00:11:58.912
I call your attention to the cooperation of Providence with the work of God.

00:11:59.584 --> 00:12:03.488
I call it the work of God to warn men against sin.

00:12:03.904 --> 00:12:05.984
And I call your attention

00:12:05.792 --> 00:12:08.320
To providence working with it

00:12:08.320 --> 00:12:14.144
To bring the preventatives and cautions of divine mercy home to men's minds.

00:12:15.296 --> 00:12:16.544
For first

00:12:16.544 --> 00:12:20.512
Observe the providence of God in sending this dream.

00:12:21.152 --> 00:12:25.632
If anything beneath the moon may be thought to be exempt from law,

00:12:25.664 --> 00:12:28.960
And to be the creature of pure chance,

00:12:29.568 --> 00:12:31.328
Surely it is a dream.

00:12:31.840 --> 00:12:32.832
True,

00:12:32.576 --> 00:12:37.888
There were in old time dreams in which God spoke to men prophetically.

00:12:38.432 --> 00:12:39.936
But ordinarily,

00:12:39.808 --> 00:12:44.352
They are the carnival of thought, a maze of mental states.

00:12:44.384 --> 00:12:46.240
A dance of disorder.

00:12:47.104 --> 00:12:51.424
The dreams which would naturally come to the wife of a Roman governor,

00:12:51.168 --> 00:12:55.968
Would not be likely to have much of tenderness or conscience in them.

00:12:55.904 --> 00:13:00.960
And would not in all probability of themselves run in the line of mercy.

00:13:01.824 --> 00:13:03.072
Dreams

00:13:02.944 --> 00:13:04.320
Ordinarily,

00:13:04.096 --> 00:13:06.816
Are the most disorderly of phenomena.

00:13:07.136 --> 00:13:11.328
And yet it seems that they are ordered of the Lord.

00:13:12.064 --> 00:13:19.296
I can well understand that every drop of spray which flashes from the wave when it dashes against the cliff

00:13:19.296 --> 00:13:23.392
Has it appointed orbit as truly as the stars of heaven?

00:13:23.936 --> 00:13:27.584
But the thoughts of men appear to be utterly lawless.

00:13:27.872 --> 00:13:32.448
Especially the thoughts of men when deep sleep falls upon them.

00:13:33.248 --> 00:13:36.640
As well might one foretell the flight of a bird.

00:13:36.640 --> 00:13:38.464
As the course of a dream.

00:13:39.296 --> 00:13:44.096
Such wild fantasies seem to be ungoverned and ungovernable.

00:13:45.088 --> 00:13:48.736
Many things operate naturally to fashion a dream.

00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:52.512
Dreams frequently depend upon the condition of the stomach.

00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:57.152
Upon the meat and drink taken by the sleeper before going to rest.

00:13:58.080 --> 00:14:00.160
They often owe their shape,

00:14:00.352 --> 00:14:02.304
To the state of the body,

00:14:02.144 --> 00:14:04.320
Or the agitation of the mind.

00:14:04.928 --> 00:14:07.456
Dreams may no doubt be caused

00:14:07.328 --> 00:14:11.040
By that which transpires in the chamber of the house,

00:14:10.880 --> 00:14:14.976
A little movement of the bed caused by passing wheels.

00:14:15.200 --> 00:14:17.600
Or the tramp of a band of men?

00:14:17.728 --> 00:14:20.032
Or the passing of a domestic,

00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:21.344
Across the floor

00:14:21.664 --> 00:14:24.992
Or even the running of a mouse behind the wainscot.

00:14:25.920 --> 00:14:28.384
May suggest and shape a dream.

00:14:29.440 --> 00:14:33.344
Any slight matter affecting the senses at such time.

00:14:33.312 --> 00:14:38.240
May raise within the slumbering mind a mob of strange ideas.

00:14:39.168 --> 00:14:42.880
Yet whatever may have operated in this lady's case,

00:14:43.136 --> 00:14:45.952
The hand of Providence was in it all.

00:14:46.336 --> 00:14:47.808
And her mind,

00:14:47.808 --> 00:14:49.824
Though fancy free.

00:14:49.824 --> 00:14:53.632
Wandered nowhere but just according to the will of God.

00:14:53.792 --> 00:14:56.512
To effect the divine purpose.

00:14:57.344 --> 00:14:59.776
She must dream just so.

00:14:59.808 --> 00:15:01.760
And know how else.

00:15:01.792 --> 00:15:03.328
And that dream

00:15:03.104 --> 00:15:06.464
Must be of such and such an order and none other.

00:15:07.328 --> 00:15:08.928
Even dreamland

00:15:08.896 --> 00:15:11.296
Knows no God but God.

00:15:12.192 --> 00:15:16.352
And even phantoms and shadows come and go at his bidding.

00:15:17.280 --> 00:15:23.264
Neither can the images of a night vision escape from the supreme authority of the most high.

00:15:24.480 --> 00:15:25.472
See,

00:15:25.216 --> 00:15:27.008
the providence of God

00:15:27.040 --> 00:15:31.520
In the fact that the dream of Pilate's wife, however, caused.

00:15:31.872 --> 00:15:34.144
Should be of such a form,

00:15:33.888 --> 00:15:37.248
And come at such a time as this.

00:15:38.176 --> 00:15:40.352
Certain old writers

00:15:40.224 --> 00:15:42.432
Trace her dream to the devil.

00:15:42.304 --> 00:15:43.712
Who thus hoped,

00:15:43.648 --> 00:15:46.304
To prevent the death of our Lord.

00:15:46.400 --> 00:15:48.960
And so prevent our redemption.

00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.808
I do not agree with the notion.

00:15:52.320 --> 00:15:54.144
But even if it were so,

00:15:54.208 --> 00:16:00.384
I admire all the more the providence which overrules even the devices of Satan.

00:16:00.320 --> 00:16:02.400
For the purposes of wisdom.

00:16:03.456 --> 00:16:04.544
Pilot.

00:16:04.416 --> 00:16:05.952
Must be warned.

00:16:06.464 --> 00:16:10.848
So that his sentence may be his own act and deed.

00:16:11.232 --> 00:16:15.072
And that warning is given him through his wife's dream.

00:16:15.680 --> 00:16:18.368
This is the way Providence works.

